{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cd28a8aa-4e26-4e19-be2d-846288f3c12e","content":"Use `Assert.ThrowsException<T>` (MSTest) or `Assert.Throws<T>` (xUnit/NUnit) instead:\n\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void CreateUser_NullEmail_ThrowsException()\n{\n    var service = new UserService();\n\n    var ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(\n        () => service.CreateUser(null, \"John\"));\n\n    Assert.AreEqual(\"email\", ex.ParamName); // optional: verify details\n}\n```\n\n**Why modernize:**\n- `[ExpectedException]` passes if *any* line throws, masking bugs (e.g., the constructor could throw instead of `CreateUser`).\n- `Assert.ThrowsException` pinpoints the exact call and lets you inspect the exception (message, properties, inner exception).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"648f5549-6b89-4cfc-b066-77cde1254db5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about modernizing a C# test that uses the `[ExpectedException]` attribute. This is a general knowledge question - no need to search the codebase.","outputTokens":256,"requestId":"1BC3:22AA1:4BCAF5:56392D:6A03D5FA"},"id":"bbd2f3bb-15c3-4caa-abb2-0a7f71680da4","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:38:08.802Z","parentId":"dba691ef-310a-47ce-928a-424621f00ec4"}
